caption: Food is decent, but DO NOT order using their own site linked on their website, BeyondMenu. They FORGOT my order and it took an hour and a half to arrive; kept getting the 'just one more minute' answer when I called, but clearly they forgot about it. Really disappointed in the service.
Before covid, they used to have free Tea.. I loved that Tea.. Momos are really good.
Delicious momos! I haven't had their curry yet though.

As a vegan it is extremely difficult to find both delicious and affordable vegan dishes in town. Momo and Curry takes the cake on both flavor and value.  $5 Veggie Momos on Wednesdays, add a split lentil soup for $3, and you have a VERY filling meal for $8 that is aromatic, spiced just right, fresh, and always always hot.  The people who work the cashiers are patient and kind.  During COVID they have taken great strides to make the pickup experience safe, including limiting the pickup “window” to 1 person at a time, just inside the door.  In normal times, it’s lovely to sit at the window and people-watch on Somerville Ave at the stools they have. :)
Love their Paneer Masala. Splurge some get some pakora, naan, and a mango lassi.
Delicious Indian food with great prices
Might be good for who haven't had real momos with the spicy chutney. I was sorely disappointed.

Good place for quick small bites. I like their Monday $4.99 momo  special. I have to update review because lately their customer service has been terrible. Always says pick up time is 25 minutes even in slower days, when get there to pick up food, it's never ready and always had to wait for 15 to 45 minutes. It's getting ridiculous as it seems they have no regards to customer time.
Great momo and pretty cheap. The sauce is very tasty as well. The veggie and the spinach paneer momo are the best!
Great prices and great amount of food. Not exactly sure why, but the momo sauce seemed a bit bland.
Incorrect hours
The menu and service were above our expectations. We really liked the environment of this restaurant. Great spot to take the family out for lunch.
Stay away from the stir fried noodles from this place.
Yum yum and spicy!

Their food was great. Took a carry out order for lunch. They have a carry out for lunch at a very reasonable rate. Quantity of food was really good. We took the vegetarian lunch which had one curry, rice and nan. The food was ready in 15 minutes. Limited seating space.
Tasty food, affordable price and huge servings.

Okay food, disappointing weekday buffet. Nice-looking place, but could be cleaner. There was a lot of food on the floor when I was there, which was surprising considering how many staff were available and how empty the place was.
Great food

I like this place have tried momos they are really good, specially the veggie ones. Also the main courses are not upto the mark I personally wouldn't try them here but the 5 stars are only for the momos as they the name starts with momo. Enjoy your plate.
Great food. Great atmosphere. Great tea.
great momos and samosa chaat. they also have free cardamom chai which is great.
The food is ok, but nothing special. Free Masala tee is a nice touch. All served as fast food on plastic plates. Quite unmemorable.

Chicken marsala with rice and the naan was good. Lots of chicken and sauce was tasty. But they forgot the utensils!!! Good thing we had one set laying around from our previous to go order. Overall it was good. I'll order it again!
Great Momo spot. The veggie Momo are delicious and I highly recommend their sauces.
Great food! Never disappointed! They also have a really good mango lassi!

I stumbled upon this while I came in the neighborhood for dosa n curry. That being closed on Monday, we went to this place. And we were surprised.  Taste was yumm. We had chicken momo 5$ special. Special entree for 9$, one was paneer masala and another one was chicken masala. Both were served with naan and rice. There was unlimited tea as well. Sip sip n sip  It also gave us enough left over for dinner.  Definitely recommended..!!

very good quality and price, better kofta than any other I tried in US, amazing paneer/spinach momo with sauce, other meals (stir fried noodles and samosa chaat) also great! definitely back whenever back in Sommerville!

Like dumplings 🥟? Momo n Curry is a spectacular place to step in and grab a bite to eat.  They’re tucked away in a nondescript area of Somerville, just outside of Boston, but it’s worth the trip.  Their Momos have beautifully thin dough which are filled with a variety of flavors and then steamed.  What to get?  The spinach Momos and the Buffalo Momo are where it’s at, but the lunch specials are also a total delight.  Don’t skimp on the sauces as they transform these delicious dumplings into something even more special.  Accompany your meal with a hot cup of spiced chai which comes free.
Testy Indian style food.. you will get free indian masala tea

It was pretty cheap and big portions. Not busy, and food was really good! There is street parking and lots of new dishes to try. Chai is free and so delicious. Only thing is they don't use real plates and silverware, so I wasn't thrilled with the amount of waste. They also only have like 3 tables.
Waited 45min for chicken Momo and then they were undercooked - totally pink in the middle. Counter guy gave me a free meal but still, yikes guys.
Nice food! Nice people and they have free tea, really good tasting tea... Loved it.. Taste of India and Nepal.. Mixed cuisines.. Amazing
Best Indian food in Somerville. Perfect spot for take out. We usually bring Momo to a local brewery. My favs are the veggie noodles, veg Momo, and their pakora.
We had the chicken Momos and chai here on a lazy Sunday morning.... Loved the food n hospitality...
Came across this Nepali and Indian restaurant by chance. Small joint but good food. Also, the masala tea they served for free tasted very good. Now I know where to go!
Authentic food!!!!
So juicy, so delicious (the momos), even without the sauces

I work across the street and go here almost daily, with zero complaints. The food is fantastic, especially the butter chicken, the lunch price is very good, and the portion sizes are large too. I've ordered take out dinner a few times as well, and they have that covered also so you really can't go wrong here.  If you want it spicy they have three levels and some dishes (like my go-to) are just inherently not spicy due to creaminess, so if you want only a little kick get it 'hot'. If you want something really spicy, you'll need to order a dish that is already spicy and then ask for it 'hot'. Today my girlfriend ordered the chicken biryani, which was pretty spicy when she ordered it 'regular' spicy, so getting that one 'hot' would be quite hot. It was also delicious so I recommend that as well!  You really can't go wrong with anything here though!

We were supposed to go to another nearby restaurant when we spotted this and thought to give it a try and we weren't disappointed. The place had good vegan options and was excellent. The prices were reasonable too.
The taste of momo was pretty bland. Even the chilli momo didn't have an authentic flavor.   The customer service wasn't good either!
Excellent momos!! I eat at least 2 plates when I go there..
Homely ambience......Nepalese n Indian cuisine.....always busy.....u can shop n park in parking of market basket across the street.....try the free "chai" .... 👍🙏🙌🥰🤗

Love this place. Food is Delicious. You can eat in or takeout. However has only limited sitting. They always have specials. I love their chicken MoMo special on Mondays. You can also enjoy free Masala tea while waiting or eating.
Momos were so good! And the biryani!
Great hole in the wall and worth the walk from Cambridge. Chicken Korma had great flavor and the Chicken Chilly Momo had a good spice level and lots of flavor from the chilly sauce. Highly recommend!
Such a great deal! Big portions, delicious food at a great price.  Highly recommend!!!

This little spot has become one of my favorites. Their food is delicious and everyone here is really nice. This is a good place to go with a couple other people or alone. It is small, so not suitable for large parties. Alternatively if you are looking for a good place for takeout, they do that too. Their momos are very flavorful and are packed full with lots of fillings, my favorite is the spinach and paneer momo. For entrees I really enjoy the mango chicken curry and the stir fried noodles. These entrees aren't too spicy, but also come with two different sauces if you want a little more heat. Their mango lassi is perfect to finish off the meal. Their chai is also very good and you can get a small cup of it free with your meal. I have come here probably a dozen times already and will definitely be coming back for more!
Delicious, try the chicken momo or the chicken tikimarsala
This place is fantastic.  Chicken Tikka Masala, Curry, Momos, Garlic Nan.  Can't go wrong with any of it.
Tasty food, big portions, cozy place, delicious baked bread and complimentary tea are highlights of this place! I recommend everyone to taste their food. Overall good restaurant
Very solid curry! Portions are generous and come with a lot of rice. The momos are also really good.

Great food, good portions. Small dinning area but they offer complementary chai which is great in those cold winter days.  One thing to keep in mind is that "very spicy" is very spice. I like spicy food but "spicy" is more than enough for most meals.
